                            <comment id="13740177" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 21:00:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test output, in case Jenkins rolls past build #444&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740291" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 22:21:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s actually just bad timing. The region servers are about to sleep for 10 seconds before re-checking for replication:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;2013-08-14 08:06:53,189 DEBUG [RS:0;vesta:43149-EventThread.replicationSource,2] regionserver.ReplicationSource(578): Replication is disabled, sleeping 100 times 10
2013-08-14 08:06:53,302 DEBUG [RS:1;vesta:39079-EventThread.replicationSource,2] regionserver.ReplicationSource(578): Replication is disabled, sleeping 100 times 10
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But we only wait 5 seconds for the row:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;2013-08-14 08:06:53,390 INFO  [Thread-2823] replication.ReplicationPeersZKImpl(123): peer 2 is enabled
2013-08-14 08:06:53,392 INFO  [Thread-2823] replication.TestReplicationSmallTests(306): Row not available
...
2013-08-14 08:06:57,902 INFO  [Thread-2823] replication.TestReplicationSmallTests(306): Row not available
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I&apos;m surprised it doesn&apos;t happen more often!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740318" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 22:34:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wait that&apos;s actually one second (default is 10 though), so why is it still sleeping?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740332" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 22:44:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In readAllEntriesToReplicateOrNextFile():&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
      LOG.trace(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Seeking in &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.currentPath + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; at position &quot;&lt;/span&gt;
          + &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.repLogReader.getPosition());
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However TRACE was not enabled for the test.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13740342" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 22:47:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah at a minimum we need to move the trace enabling to TestReplicationBase instead of TestReplicationKillRS.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740348" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 22:51:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is where IOE was thrown in DFSClient:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;synchronized&lt;/span&gt; void seek(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; targetPos) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (targetPos &amp;gt; getFileLength()) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; IOException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Cannot seek after EOF&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In ReplicationSource#run():&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (readAllEntriesToReplicateOrNextFile(currentWALisBeingWrittenTo)) {
          &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt;;
        }
      } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (IOException ioe) {
        LOG.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.peerClusterZnode + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; Got: &quot;&lt;/span&gt;, ioe);
        gotIOE = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ioe.getCause() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; EOFException) {
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should we cover the case of &quot;Cannot seek after EOF&quot; along with EOFException ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740360" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 22:54:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How about this patch ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740366" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 22:57:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What would doing this get us? And shouldn&apos;t we just not go over the EOF in the first place? That seems more interesting to me as it sounds like there&apos;s a bug in the position tracking logic.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740368" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 22:58:21 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;shouldn&apos;t we just not go over the EOF in the first place?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I agree.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740383" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 23:10:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How about we enable TRACE logging, using patch v2, for now and keep the JIRA open ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The next time we see similar error we should have more clue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740389" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 23:17:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would rather have another jira for that since Stack is cutting a RC tonight, and TestReplicationKillRS will need a imports cleanup.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740405" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 23:27:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If I understand your comments correctly, I will:&lt;br/&gt;
1. create a JIRA for the LOG level change with patch v3&lt;br/&gt;
2. link that JIRA to this JIRA&lt;br/&gt;
3. Once Hadoop QA passes for JIRA in #1, I will check into 0.95 and trunk&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How does the above look to you ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740469" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 15 Aug 2013 00:10:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740472" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 15 Aug 2013 00:17:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Logged &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9225&quot; title=&quot;Enable TRACE logging in TestReplicationBase&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-9225&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-9225&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for LOG level change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13750361" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 26 Aug 2013 18:24:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Did you see it failing again?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13764487" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 11 Sep 2013 17:02:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t seen the test fail so far.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13777743" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 16:59:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Feel free to reopen if the test fails again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
